EXAMPLE 2 Sketch the graph of the function f(x) = x² + 6x + 10.
SOLUTION Completing the square, we write the equation of the graph as
y = x² + 6x + 10 = (x + 3)² + 1
This means we obtain the desired graph by starting with the parabola y = x² and shifting
3 units to the left and then 1 unit upward (see Figure 5).
